{
  "texts": [
    "This prefix can be used to instruct the language model about the expected output language (e.g., write the prefix like \"Respuesta:\" to suggest answers written in Spanish) or the output format (e.g., to suggest the output to be formatted in XML).",
    "Code generation for prompt executionThe Impromptu editor provides a functionality to autogenerate a Python file containing the minimum required code for querying a generative AI system with a prompt in the proper input format expected by the AI provider.",
    "Currently, the editor supports the generation of code for OpenAI's ChatGPT and Stable Diffusion models, by accessing their available respective APIs.",
    "The Python code defines an abstract class PromptService with a public method execute_prompt() that first queries the model and collects its response (abstract template method query_model()), and then validates its output (see Section 4.3).",
    "The template for this abstract class contains placeholders for injecting the prompt generated by the tool and its media output type.Depending on the user selection, the generated code includes a concrete class that implements PromptService and its query_model() template method with the specifics of the model provider."
  ]
}